The paper deals with computer vision and robotics, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) sub-categories. The paper also discusses lifelong learning, which is a topic in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper evaluates state-of-the-art algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing for providing a dataset and benchmark, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category.
